IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROMOTE THE PRINCIPLES OF THE VETERANS OF FOREIGN WARS OF THE UNITED STATES. THESE OBJECTIVES ARE FRATERNAL, PATRIOTIC, HISTORICAL, CHARITABLE AND EDUCATIONAL; TO PRESERVE AND STRENGTHEN COMRADESHIP AMONG ITS MEMBERS; TO ASSIST WORTHY COMRADES; TO PERPETUATE THE MEMORY AND HISTORY OF OUR DEAD, AND TO ASSIST THEIR SURVIVING SPOUSES AND ORPHANS; TO MAINTAIN TRUE ALLEGIANCE TO THE GOVERNMENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA AND FIDELITY TO ITS CONSTITUTION AND LAWS; TO FOSTER TRUE PATRIOTISM; TO MAINTAIN AND EXTEND THE INSTITUTIONS OF AMERICAN FREEDOM, AND TO PRESERVE AND DEFEND THE UNITED STATES FROM ALL ENEMIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE PURPOSE OF THIS CORPORATION SHALL BE FRATERNAL, PATRIOTIC, HISTORICAL, CHARITABLE, AND EDUCATIONAL; TO PRESERVE AND STRENGTHEN COMRADESHIP AMONG ITS MEMBERS; TO ASSIST WORTHY COMRADES; TO PERPETUATE THE MEMORY AND HISTORY OF OUR DEAD; AND TO ASSIST THEIR WIDOWS AND ORPHANS; TO MAINTAIN TRUE ALLEGIANCE TO THE GOVERNMENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, AND FIDELITY TO ITS CONSTITUTION AND LAWS; TO FOSTER TRUE PATRIOTISM; TO MAINTAIN AND EXTEND THE INSTITUTIONS OF AMERICAN FREEDOM; AND TO PRESERVE AND DEFEND THE UNITED STATES FROM ALL HER ENEMIES.
IRS990.Desc: THE VETERANS OF FOREIGN WARS MAINTAINS COOPERATION AND COORDINATION OF EFFORTS BETWEEN ALL POSTS WITHIN WISCONSIN AND CARRIES OUT NATIONAL AND DEPARTMENT ORDERS, PROGRAMS, AND POLICIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE VETERANS OF FOREIGN WARS PUBLISHES A NEWSLETTER TO INFORM ITS MEMBERS OF CURRENT EVENTS OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE NEWSLETTER IS DISTRIBUTED TO APPROXIMATELY 25,466 MEMBERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE VETERANS OF FOREIGN WARS AWARDED $9,250 IN SCHOLARSHIPS TO 17 RECIPIENTS, PROVIDED EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE TOTALING $65,841 TO 42 VETERANS AND ASSISTING 4 VETERANS OR FAMILIES OF VETERANS WITH $3,000 IN DISASTER RELIEF.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE VETERANS OF FOREIGN WARS DEPARTMENT OF WISCONSIN REVIEWS APPLICATIONS AND REQUESTS FOR ASSISTANCE AS BEING HONORABLE AND GENERALLY DOES NOT CONDUCT ADDITIONAL MONITORING OF THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS ONCE THE FUNDS HAVE BEEN DISBURSED TO THE INTENDED RECIPIENTS. FUNDS ARE GENERALLY DISBURSED DIRECTLY TO THE CREDITOR OR COMPANY REQUIRING PAYMENT RATHER THAN TO THE INDIVIDUAL REQUESTING ASSISTANCE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S MEMBERSHIP IS BASED ON CAMPAIGN MEDAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION HAVE THE RIGHT TO VOTE AT ALL LEVELS FOR OFFICERS TO REPRESENT THEM ON THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NATIONAL HEADQUARTERS HAVE FINAL APPROVAL OF ANY CHANGES TO THE CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PREPARED FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE QUARTERMASTER BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNUALLY ALL DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS COMPLETE AND SIGN A STATEMENT THAT PROVIDES INFORMATION REGARDING THEIR INTERESTS AND THOSE OF THEIR FAMILY MEMBERS THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS. THE MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY MAKE DETERMINATIONS OF WHETHER A CONFLICT EXISTS AND REVIEW ACTUAL CONFLICTS. ANY PERSON WITH A CONFLICT IS PROHIBITED FROM PARTICIPATING IN THE GOVERNING BODY'S DELIBERATIONS AND DECISIONS IN THE TRANSACTION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE STATE COMMANDER IS RESPONSIBLE FOR PERFORMING AN ANNUAL EVALUATION OF THE STATE/ADJUTANT QUARTERMASTER AND DETERMINING THE STATE/ADJUTANT QUARTERMASTER'S COMPENSATION. DATA ON COMPENSATION PAID BY COMPARABLE ORGANIZATIONS FOR SIMILAR SERVICES IS USED IN MAKING THIS DETERMINATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MADE ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
